{
    "id": "1cb117f7-d626-704b-31d4-baec573e6729",
    "answerInContext": true,
    "answer": "No, the economy did not shrink after the Omicron variant arrived. In fact, due to the rapid distribution of COVID-19 vaccines, the Omicron variant did not cause significant economic disruption. The GDP grew 7% in 2021, despite the arrival of the Delta and Omicron variants and the global supply chain shortages, which were largely fueled by the dramatic upswing in consumer spending and the shift in that spend from services to goods."
}

